o Hsieh","line":127},{"title":"Author/Chun-Wei Lu","target":"Author/Chun-Wei Lu","line":128},{"title":"Author/Chien-Chang Lu","target":"Author/Chien-Chang Lu","line":129},{"title":"Author/Chien-Chang Lu","target":"Author/Chien-Chang Lu","line":130},{"title":"Author/Ko-Chao Lee","target":"Author/Ko-Chao Lee","line":131},{"title":"Author/Ko-Chao Lee","target":"Author/Ko-Chao Lee","line":132},{"title":"Author/Ko-Chao Lee","target":"Author/Ko-Chao Lee","line":133},{"title":"Author/Ko-Chao Lee","target":"Author/Ko-Chao Lee","line":134},{"title":"Author/Li-Ya Lee","target":"Author/Li-Ya Lee","line":135},{"title":"Author/Li-Ya Lee","target":"Author/Li-Ya Lee","line":136},{"title":"Author/Wanping Chen","target":"Author/Wanping Chen","line":137},{"title":"Author/Wan-Ping Chen","target":"Author/Wan-Ping Chen","line":138},{"title":"Author/Wan-Ping Chen","target":"Author/Wan-Ping Chen","line":139},{"title":"Author/Chen Chin-Chu","target":"Author/Chen Chin-Chu","line":140},{"title":"Author/Chin-Chu Chen","target":"Author/Chin-Chu Chen","line":141},{"title":"Author/Chin-Chu Chen","target":"Author/Chin-Chu Chen","line":142},{"title":"Author/Chen Chin-Chu","target":"Author/Chen Chin-Chu","line":143},{"title":"Author/Wen-Shih Huang","target":"Author/Wen-Shih Huang","line":144},{"title":"Author/Wen-Shih Huang","target":"Author/Wen-Shih Huang","line":145},{"title":"Author/Hsing-Chun Kuo","target":"Author/Hsing-Chun Kuo","line":146},{"title":"Author/Hsing-Chun Kuo","target":"Author/Hsing-Chun Kuo","line":147},{"title":"Author/Hsing-Chun Kuo","target":"Author/Hsing-Chun Kuo","line":148},{"title":"PDF","target":"biblib/lee_protective_2014/lee_protective_2014.pdf","line":150}],"metadata":{"id":"lee_protective_2014","type":"article-journal","title":"Protective Effects of Hericium erinaceus Mycelium and Its Isolated Erinacine A against Ischemia-Injury-Induced Neuronal Cell Death via the Inhibition of iNOS/p38 MAPK and Nitrotyrosine","issued":{"date-parts":[[2014]]},"DOI":"10.3390/ijms150915073","container-title":"International Journal of Molecular Sciences","abstract":"Hericium erinaceus, an edible mushroom, has been demonstrated to potentiate the effects of numerous biological activities. The aim of this study was to investigate whether H. erinaceus mycelium could act as an anti-inflammatory agent to bring about neuroprotection using a model of global ischemic stroke and the mechanisms involved. Rats were treated with H. erinaceus mycelium and its isolated diterpenoid derivative, erinacine A, after ischemia reperfusion brain injuries caused by the occlusion of the two common carotid arteries. The production of inflammatory cytokines in serum and the infracted volume of the brain were measured. The proteins from the stroke animal model (SAM) were evaluated to determine the effect of H. erinaceus mycelium. H. erinaceus mycelium reduced the total infarcted volumes by 22% and 44% at a concentration of 50 and 300 mg/kg, respectively, compared to the SAM group. The levels of acute inflammatory cytokines, including interleukin-1β, interleukin-6 and tumor necrosis factor a, were all reduced by erinacine A. Levels of nitrotyrosine-containing proteins, phosphorylation of p38 MAPK and CCAAT enhancer-binding protein (C/EBP) and homologous protein (CHOP) expression were attenuated by erinacine A. Moreover, the modulation of ischemia injury factors present in the SAM model by erinacine A seemed to result in the suppression of reactive nitrogen species and the downregulation of inducible NO synthase (iNOS), p38 MAPK and CHOP. These findings confirm the nerve-growth properties of Hericium erinaceus mycelium, which include the prevention of ischemic injury to neurons; this protective effect seems to be involved in the in vivo activity of iNOS, p38 MAPK and CHOP.","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Lee","given":"Kam-Fai","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Kam-Fai","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Jiann-Hwa","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Jiann-Hwa","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Jiann-Hwa","literal":""},{"family":"Teng","given":"Chiao-Fang","literal":""},{"family":"Teng","given":"Chih-Chuan","literal":""},{"family":"Shen","given":"Chien-Heng","literal":""},{"family":"Shen","given":"Chien-Heng","literal":""},{"family":"Hsieh","given":"Meng-Che","literal":""},{"family":"Hsieh","given":"Meng-Chiao","literal":""},{"family":"Lu","given":"Chun-Wei","literal":""},{"family":"Lu","given":"Chien-Chang","literal":""},{"family":"Lu","given":"Chien-Chang","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Ko-Chao","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Ko-Chao","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Ko-Chao","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Ko-Chao","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Li-Ya","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Li-Ya","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Wanping","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Wan-Ping","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Wan-Ping","literal":""},{"family":"Chin-Chu","given":"Chen","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Chin-Chu","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Chin-Chu","literal":""},{"family":"Chin-Chu","given":"Chen","literal":""},{"family":"Huang","given":"Wen-Shih","literal":""},{"family":"Huang","given":"Wen-Shih","literal":""},{"family":"Kuo","given":"Hsing-Chun","literal":""},{"family":"Kuo","given":"Hsing-Chun","literal":""},{"family":"Kuo","given":"Hsing-Chun","literal":""}],"citation-key":"lee_protective_2014","year":"2014","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["Protective Effects of Hericium erinaceus Mycelium and Its Isolated Erinacine A against Ischemia-Injury-Induced Neuronal Cell Death via the Inhibition of iNOS/p38 MAPK and Nitrotyrosine"],"author-links":["[[Author/Kam-Fai Lee]]","[[Author/Kam-Fai Lee]]","[[Author/Jiann-Hwa Chen]]","[[Author/Jiann-Hwa Chen]]","[[Author/Jiann-Hwa Chen]]","[[Author/Chiao-Fang Teng]]","[[Author/Chih-Chuan Teng]]","[[Author/Chien-Heng Shen]]","[[Author/Chien-Heng Shen]]"